[ NETWORK ]

  - The dhcpcd is not configured by default because of security reasons.
    either use 'systemctl start dhcpcd' to start manually or 'systemctl enable
    dhcpcd' to enable and start during boot up.

[ INSTALL ]

  - To install BlackArch Linux simply run 'blackarch-install' and follow the
    instructions.

[ EXPLOITS ]

  - A collection of exploits can be found in /usr/share/exploits. To update the
    archive use 'sploitctl'.

[ MISC ]

  - A ChangeLog file of the ISO can be found in /root.
  - Remember: HACK THE PLANET, D00R THE PLANET, RULE THE PLANET!
